      "content": "Neosporin is a good choice for keeping the wound clean. If the redness starts spreading, you can apply a thin layer of Neosporin, but don't double up too much. It's best to use it as directed. Adding hydrogen peroxide to the cleaning routine is not typically recommended, as it can irritate the wound and delay healing. Stick to Neosporin and keep the wound clean and dry. If the redness spreads significantly, or you develop a fever, then you should definitely seek medical attention to prevent a possible infection from getting worse. Your health is important, and a doctor visit might be necessary if the situation doesn't improve.",
